slidelink.displaytext: Students have an array of experiences that they bring with them to university, including basic expectations when it comes to service and how they want to be treated. We should consider this when aiming to provide quality service when interacting with a student.

I understand that you expected to have this issue resolved yesterday. I want to assist you in resolving this issue as quickly as possible. I would like to investigate the issue a bit further, as well as work internally with my colleagues to resolve the issue. Is it okay if I follow-up with you by the end of the business day to provide you with a status update?
Yes, that will be helpful. Thank you.

By providing clear directions on how the problem will be handled, the student does not need to go on a hunt to try to find answers. Having someone who will be true to their word and will provide timely answers will build the student’s confidence in the university.
Module 2: Anatomy of a Buckeye Link call
Practice your opening script by mimicking the expressions on the characters faces.
Good morning. Thank you for calling Undergraduate Admissions, this is _______. How can I help you today?
Thank you for calling Undergraduate Admissions, this is _______. How can I help you?
Good morning! Thank you for calling Undergraduate Admissions, this is _______. How may I help you?
Did you notice how speaking with a smile on your face really does sound more engaging?
Now it is time to develop the scripts you will use for placing a caller on hold.
I’d like to place you on a brief hold while I research your account. Is that okay?

What are some other ways you could ask the caller to hold while you research?
Remember to thank the caller for holding upon returning.
We want to end our calls on a holistic and positive note. Practice how you would end your call.
Is there anything else I can assist you with today?
No, you have addressed all of my concerns.
Great, thanks for calling and I hope you have a wonderful day!

Asking “Is there anything else I can help you with today?” or “If you think of any additional questions or concerns, please feel free to contact us again” will allow the caller the opportunity to address any lingering concerns. In addition to wrapping up the call holistically, we also want to thank them for calling.
